9:30Z", "author_association": "NONE", "body_html": "<h2>To Reproduce</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre>a <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> T.zeros(<span class=\"pl-c1\">5</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">requires_grad</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)\nb <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> T.zeros(<span class=\"pl-c1\">5</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">requires_grad</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)\nF.mse_loss(a,b)\n<span class=\"pl-c\"><span class=\"pl-c\">#</span> OK</span>\n\na <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> T.zeros(<span class=\"pl-c1\">5</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>)\nb <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> T.zeros(<span class=\"pl-c1\">5</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>)\nF.mse_loss(a,b)\n<span class=\"pl-c\"><span class=\"pl-c\">#</span> RuntimeError: input and target shapes do not match: input [5 x 1 x 10], target [5 x 10 x 10] at /opt/conda/conda-bld/pytorch_1524577523076/work/aten/src/THNN/generic/MSECriterion.c:13</span></pre></div>\n<h2>Expected behavior</h2>\n<p>Broadcast should work the same as with grad.</p>\n<h2>Workaround</h2>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre><span class=\"pl-c\"><span class=\"pl-c\">#</span> assumes size_average=False</span>\n<span class=\"pl-k\">def</span> <span class=\"pl-en\">my_mse</span>(<span class=\"pl-smi\">a</span>,<span class=\"pl-smi\">b</span>):\n    <span class=\"pl-k\">return</span> ((a<span class=\"pl-k\">-</span>b)<span class=\"pl-k\">**</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">2</span>).sum()</pre></div>", "body_text": "To Reproduce\na = T.zeros(5,1,10, requires_grad=True)\nb = T.zeros(5,10,10, requires_grad=True)\nF.mse_loss(a,b)\n# OK\n\na = T.zeros(5,1,10)\nb = T.zeros(5,10,10)\nF.mse_loss(a,b)\n# RuntimeError: input and target shapes do not match: input [5 x 1 x 10], target [5 x 10 x 10] at /opt/conda/conda-bld/pytorch_1524577523076/work/aten/src/THNN/generic/MSECriterion.c:13\nExpected behavior\nBroadcast should work the same as with grad.\nWorkaround\n# assumes size_average=False\ndef my_mse(a,b):\n    return ((a-b)**2).sum()", "body": "## To Reproduce\r\n\r\n```python\r\na = T.zeros(5,1,10, requires_grad=True)\r\nb = T.zeros(5,10,10, requires_grad=True)\r\nF.mse_loss(a,b)\r\n# OK\r\n\r\na = T.zeros(5,1,10)\r\nb = T.zeros(5,10,10)\r\nF.mse_loss(a,b)\r\n# RuntimeError: input and target shapes do not match: input [5 x 1 x 10], target [5 x 10 x 10] at /opt/conda/conda-bld/pytorch_1524577523076/work/aten/src/THNN/generic/MSECriterion.c:13\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected behavior\r\n\r\nBroadcast should work the same as with grad.\r\n\r\n## Workaround\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# assumes size_average=False\r\ndef my_mse(a,b):\r\n    return ((a-b)**2).sum()\r\n```"}